const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How much does a basic computer diagnostic cost in Romford?',
    answer:
      'At Chiltern Computers in Harold Hill, I charge £20 for a diagnostic assessment. If I fix the issue during the diagnostic, that\'s all you pay. If the repair requires more work, I\'ll quote you separately and waive the diagnostic fee if you go ahead.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Why do computer repair prices vary so much?',
    answer:
      'Prices vary based on the complexity of the problem, the parts needed, and whether it\'s a laptop or desktop. A straightforward virus removal is cheaper than a motherboard-level repair because of the time and expertise involved. Always ask for a quote before agreeing to any work.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is it cheaper to repair a computer or buy a new one?',
    answer:
      'In most cases, repair is significantly cheaper. An SSD upgrade for £60-£120 can make a slow computer feel brand new, compared to £400-£800 for a replacement. Repair only stops making sense when costs exceed about 50% of a new equivalent, or the machine is very old with multiple issues.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you charge if you can\'t fix the problem?',
    answer:
      'I operate a no fix, no fee policy on repairs. The only charge you\'ll pay if I can\'t resolve the issue is the initial diagnostic fee, which covers my time examining the machine. I\'ll always be upfront about whether a fix is possible before doing any paid work.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Are computer repair costs in Essex higher than online services?',
    answer:
      'Local repair shops like mine in Harold Hill are often comparable to or cheaper than online services, and you get the advantage of face-to-face service, faster turnaround, and no shipping risks. You also know exactly who is handling your data and your machine.',
  },
];
