            One of the most common questions I get asked at my workshop in Harold Hill is: <strong>"How much is this going to cost me?"</strong> It's a fair question, and one that deserves an honest answer. The trouble is, too many repair shops in Romford and across Essex are vague about pricing until they've already got your machine on the bench.
          </p>

          <p>
            I've been repairing computers since 2007, and I believe in complete pricing transparency. So here's a straightforward breakdown of what common repairs actually cost, what affects the price, and how to avoid overpaying.
          </p>

          <h2 class="space-font">Common Repair Costs at a Glance</h2>

          <p>
            These are the prices you can expect at Chiltern Computers for the most common jobs. You can also see my full <a href="/pricing/" style="color: var(--plasma-cyan);">pricing page</a> for more detail.
          </p>

